      Constructs a new swerve based drivetrain.
      Parameters:
      config - The configuration values for the drivetrain's characteristics and behavior, passed in as a "BreakerSwerveDriveConfig" object
      swerveModules - The swerve drive modules that make up the drivetrain. Should be passed in the same oreder as the translations in your BreakerSwerveDriveConfig

  • Method Details

    • setRawModuleStates

      public void setRawModuleStates​(edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.SwerveModuleState... targetModuleStates)
      Sets each module to match a target module state in the order they were passed in. Automaticly optimizes and desaturates wheelspeeds, stops module if set speed is below module speed deadband threshold

      NOTE: Not affected by slow mode.

    • move

      public void move​(edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds robotRelativeVelocities, boolean useSlowMode)
      Standard drivetrain movement command. Specifies robot velocity in each axis including robot rotation (rad/sec).

      NOTE: All values are relative to the robot's orientation.

      Parameters:
      robotRelativeVelocities - ChassisSpeeds object representing the robots velocities in each axis relative to its local reference frame.
      useSlowMode - Whether or not to apply the set slow mode multiplier to the given speeds.

    • move

      public void move​(edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.ChassisSpeeds robotRelativeVelocities)
      Standard drivetrain movement command, specifies robot velocity in each axis including robot rotation (rad/sec). Slow mode is active based on whener or not the user has globaly enabled slow mode.

      NOTE: All values are relative to the robot's orientation.

      Parameters:
      robotRelativeVelocities - ChassisSpeeds object representing the robots velocities in each axis relative to its local reference frame.

    • move

      public void move​(double forwardVelMetersPerSec, double horizontalVelMetersPerSec, double radPerSec)

      NOTE: All values are relative to the robot's orientation.

      Parameters:

      horizontalVelMetersPerSec - Sideways movement velocity in m/s.
